# FontPair AI - Environment Variables

# ============================================
# GEMINI API KEY (Cloud AI)
# ============================================
# Get your free API key from: https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey
# Used for cloud-based font analysis with Google's Gemini model
# Free tier: 15 requests/min, 1M tokens/day
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_gemini_api_key_here

# ============================================
# SUPABASE LICENSE SYSTEM
# ============================================
# Supabase project URL (e.g., https://xxxxx.supabase.co)
# Create a free Supabase project at: https://supabase.com
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=your_supabase_project_url_here

# Supabase anonymous (public) key
# Find this in your Supabase project settings under API > Project API keys > anon public
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_supabase_anon_key_here

# ============================================
# OPTIONAL: GUMROAD INTEGRATION
# ============================================
# URL where users can purchase licenses (displayed in LicenseKeyScreen)
# VITE_GUMROAD_PURCHASE_URL=https://gumroad.com/your-product-link

# ============================================
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
# ============================================
# 1. Copy this file to .env.local
# 2. Replace placeholder values with your actual keys
# 3. Run the Supabase schema: supabase-schema.sql in your Supabase SQL editor
# 4. Restart the dev server: npm run dev
#
# SECURITY NOTES:
# - Never commit .env.local to version control (it's in .gitignore)
# - The GEMINI_API_KEY is used server-side (not exposed to browser)
# - VITE_* prefixed variables are exposed to the browser client
# - Supabase RLS policies protect sensitive data
# - License keys are validated server-side via Supabase RPC functions
